<p>Ottawa is the capital of Canada and is on the border of Ontario and Quebec. The Ottawa River defines the border and in the photograph below, Ontario is on the left and Quebec on the right.</p>

<p>Their parliament was built in Victorian times in a gothic style and the buildings are beautiful. Here is another panorama with parliament in the foreground and Quebec across the river.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/2010/02/4331807503_15c81c5a1f_o.jpg" alt="" class="align-center" /></p>

<p>Canadians are generally very nice people but out on the ice hockey rink they show their true colours. In hockey, fighting is encouraged and it is sort of like kendo on ice. The other popular sport is curling which looks about as much fun as mowing the lawn. It was so boring I didnâ€™t watch it long enough to see a fight.</p>

<p>The worldâ€™s longest skating rink at 8km in length is formed in Rideau canal. Iâ€™m told that students skate between Ottawa University and Carleton University to attend their classes.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/images/2010/02/4332887868_799c308f80_o.jpg" alt="" class="align-center" /></p>

